---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Features — SnapInspect AI"
  description="Voice dictation, AI-polished findings, AI client summaries, branded PDF reports, 23 inspection categories, photo capture, comment library, and more."
  ogPath="/features"
>
  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────── HERO ─── -->
  <section class="border-b border-[var(--color-line-soft)]">
    <div class="container-editorial pt-16 pb-20 md:pt-24 md:pb-28">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-16 reveal reveal-1">
        <span class="label">№ 002 — Features</span>
        <span class="label">Volume I</span>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-2">
          <p class="chapter-mark">SECTION</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <h1 class="font-display text-[clamp(3rem,8vw,7rem)] leading-[0.95] reveal reveal-2">
            Every tool, in its <em class="text-[var(--color-rust)]">right place</em>.
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-10 text-xl text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] leading-relaxed max-w-2xl reveal reveal-3">
            A working inspector needs a fast, opinionated app — not a configuration project. Here is what's inside SnapInspect AI, and why each part exists.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────── 01 AI POLISH ─── -->
  <section class="border-b border-[var(--color-line-soft)] py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="container-editorial">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-center">
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-6">
          <p class="chapter-mark mb-6">01 — AI POLISH</p>
          <h2 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl leading-[0.95] mb-8">
            Rough notes,<br/>
            <em class="text-[var(--color-navy)]">finished prose.</em>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] leading-relaxed mb-6 max-w-xl">
            Tap "Polish with AI" on any finding. The text becomes contractor-grade language inspectors actually use. Conservative. Specific. Never invents a measurement or recommends a repair you didn't suggest.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] leading-relaxed max-w-xl mb-8">
            When the original note is too brief to be defensible, the AI flags it and asks you to add detail. Re-polish freely until it reads right.
          </p>
          <p class="annotation">
            "Most polish requests complete in under three seconds."
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-5 md:col-start-8">
          <div class="phone-frame max-w-sm mx-auto">
            <img src="/screenshots/4-finding-after-ai.png" alt="AI Polish" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────── 02 AI SUMMARY ─── -->
  <section class="border-b border-[var(--color-line-soft)] py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-paper-soft)]">
    <div class="container-editorial">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-center">
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-5 order-2 md:order-1">
          <div class="phone-frame max-w-sm mx-auto">
            <img src="/screenshots/5-pdf-report.png" alt="PDF report" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-6 md:col-start-7 order-1 md:order-2">
          <p class="chapter-mark mb-6">02 — AI CLIENT SUMMARY</p>
          <h2 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl leading-[0.95] mb-8">
            The homeowner page<br/>
            <em class="text-[var(--color-rust)]">that gets read.</em>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] leading-relaxed mb-6 max-w-xl">
            Every PDF opens with a green-yellow-red client summary written by the AI from your findings. It explains what was found, why it matters, what could happen, and which specialist to call.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
            Realtors and buyers actually read this page. It is the difference between a report that earns a referral and one that doesn't.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────── 03 BRANDING ─── -->
  <section class="border-b border-[var(--color-line-soft)] py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="container-editorial">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-7">
          <p class="chapter-mark mb-6">03 — BRANDING</p>
          <h2 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl leading-[0.95] mb-8">
            The report carries<br/>
            <em class="text-[var(--color-navy)]">your name.</em>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] leading-relaxed mb-6 max-w-xl">
            Your company logo. Your license number. Your signature. Your brand color. The PDF the buyer receives is a finished business document, not a SaaS template.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-3 text-[15px]">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--color-rust)]">—</span>Company logo</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--color-rust)]">—</span>License number</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--color-rust)]">—</span>Signature</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--color-rust)]">—</span>Brand color throughout</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--color-rust)]">—</span>Custom default disclaimer</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--color-rust)]">—</span>Cover, scope, summary, findings</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-4 md:col-start-9">
          <div class="border border-[var(--color-line)] bg-[var(--color-paper-soft)] p-8">
            <p class="label mb-4">EXAMPLE</p>
            <div class="border-t border-[var(--color-line)] pt-6">
              <p class="font-display text-2xl mb-1 italic">Watkins Inspections, LLC</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-gray)] mb-6">Lic. № HI-1238104 · 2026</p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-xs text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
                <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Property —</strong> 1842 Oak Ridge Way</p>
                <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Client —</strong> Ana Restrepo</p>
                <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Inspector —</strong> Marcus Watkins</p>
                <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Date —</strong> March 18, 2026</p>
              </div>
              <div class="mt-6 pt-4 border-t border-[var(--color-line-soft)]">
                <p class="label text-[var(--color-rust)]">PDF EXPORT · 14 PAGES</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────── FULL LEDGER ─── -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 border-b border-[var(--color-line-soft)]">
    <div class="container-editorial">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 mb-16">
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
          <p class="chapter-mark">№ 004 — The Inventory</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-8 md:col-start-5">
          <h2 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl leading-[0.95]">
            Everything else,<br/>
            <em>itemized.</em>
          </h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-10">
        {[
          { label: "VOICE", title: "Hands-free dictation", body: "Tap the microphone on any field. Speech-to-text runs locally when possible. Works at the top of a ladder or under a crawlspace." },
          { label: "PHOTOS", title: "Capture and annotate", body: "Take photos from anywhere in the inspection. File them to a finding or a category. Photos never leave the device unless you share the report." },
          { label: "CATEGORIES", title: "Twenty-three categories", body: "Roof, Exterior, Foundation, Grading, Driveway, Garage, Structure, Basement, Attic, Bedrooms, Kitchen, Bathrooms, Plumbing, Electrical, HVAC, and more — organized the way you actually inspect." },
          { label: "SEVERITY", title: "Five-state severity", body: "Information, Minor, Moderate, Major, Safety Hazard. Color-coded throughout the app and on the final report." },
          { label: "PROGRESS", title: "Per-category status", body: "Inspected, Not Present, Not Inspected. The dashboard shows a progress ring so you always know what's left." },
          { label: "LIBRARY", title: "Seventy comment templates", body: "Conservative pre-written comments seeded on first launch. Save your own as you write. Search and tap to insert." },
          { label: "OFFLINE", title: "Sync when reconnected", body: "Inspect anywhere. If a finding can't be polished because you're offline, it queues and finishes when you're back online." },
          { label: "SHARE", title: "iOS share sheet", body: "Send the PDF directly to Mail, Messages, AirDrop, Files, or any iOS share target. No proprietary portal to log into." },
        ].map((f) => (
          <article class="border-t border-[var(--color-line)] pt-6">
            <p class="label mb-3">{f.label}</p>
            <h3 class="font-display text-2xl mb-3 leading-tight">{f.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-[15px] text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] leading-relaxed">{f.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────── CTA ─── -->
  <section class="py-32 md:py-40">
    <div class="container-editorial text-center">
      <p class="chapter-mark mb-8">— FIN —</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-7xl leading-[0.95] max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-10">
        Try it for <em class="text-[var(--color-rust)]">two weeks</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] mb-10 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        SnapInspect Pro is $99.99 per month with a 14-day free trial. Cancel any time in the App Store.
      </p>
      <a href="https://apps.apple.com" class="btn-primary text-base px-8 py-4">
        Download on the App Store
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
